    "Research Question 3: How accurate are the predictions for extreme values?The Table 6 provides a detailed comparison of the TXtreme's performance on extreme and normal values across various datasets, highlighting its effectiveness in predicting extreme points.",
    "This enhanced performance is due to the integration of a classifier and an extreme value indicator within the model architecture.",
    "These components enable the model to identify and specifically focus on extreme events, thereby improving its predictive accuracy for such occurrences.",
    "For the Solar dataset, the TXtreme achieves an extreme RMSE of 8.21 and an extreme MAE of 3.88, contributing to a total RMSE of 6.10 and a total MAE of 3.10.",
    "This indicates the model's strong ability to handle both normal and extreme values effectively."
